====Derived terms====
*പള്ളീലച്ഛന് [paɭːiːlatʃːhan]..........Christian priest.
*വല്ല്യച്ഛന്  [ʋalːjatʃːhan]..........Older paternal uncle. Literally "big father".
*കൊച്ചച്ഛന് [kotʃatʃːhan]..........Younger paternal uncle. Literally "small father".
====Synonyms====

* പിതാവ് [piθaːʋ]..........This word was derived from Sanskrit ''pitar'' and is considered very formal.
* തന്ത [θaɳθa]..........This is a very colloquial and rude term meaning father.
* ബാപ്പ [baːpːa]..........This is the word that most Muslims who speak malayalam use for father.
* അപ്പന് [apːan] ''or'' അപ്പച്ചന് [apːatʃːan].......... These are usually used by Christians who use അച്ഛന് to refer to priests (with irregular vocative അച്ഛോ [atʃːoː] most of the time).

